UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1611
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Charles
2 William Kennedy.
3 WHEREAS, Charles William "Mickey" Kennedy was born on October 17, 1939, to
4 William Edward Kennedy, Sr., and Macie Smith Kennedy, who preceded him in death;
5 and
6 WHEREAS, Mickey Kennedy was educated in the Jefferson County Public School
7 system and graduated from Central High School in 1957; and
8 WHEREAS, Mickey Kennedy proudly served his country in the United States
9 Army as a military policeman; and
10 WHEREAS, Mickey Kennedy loved the Lord, and was deeply involved in his
11 beloved church, Stoner Memorial AME Zion, where he took on many volunteer
12 positions; and
13 WHEREAS, Mickey Kennedy enjoyed many hobbies including motorcycle riding,
14 photography, fitness, upholstery, and bowling; and
15 WHEREAS, Mickey Kennedy deeply loved his family, including his brother,
16 Edward Kennedy, Jr., and sister, Macie Nanette Becker, who preceded him in death, and
17 his surviving family members including his wife, Dorothy; his children, Roderick
18 "Waynie" (Daphne) Jones; and Andra "Neecie" Carroll; siblings, Lula (William) Howard;
19 Kenneth (Elsie) Kennedy; Kathryn Wallace; Margie (William) Wilson; and Eva (Jim)
20 Green; grandchildren, Alyssia Jones, Ashley Jones, Tyler (Brittany) Carroll, and Julian
21 Carroll; and many nieces, nephews, cousins, and friends; and
22 WHEREAS, Charles William Kennedy passed from this earthly life on December
23 3, 2025, to the sweet embrace of his Lord; and
24 WHEREAS, Charles William Kennedy will be fondly remembered for the many
25 contributions he made to his country, community, and family, and will be deeply missed
26 by all those who knew him.
27 NOW, THEREFORE,
Page 1 of 2
